        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 7:04PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 703 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Saratoga Springs, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Saratoga Springs around 710 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Deans Corners, Center
White Creek, Grangerville, Kings Station, Northumberland, Wayville,
Middle Falls, North Cambridge, Halls Corner, and Mannings Cove.

People attending Saratoga Performing Arts Center (SPAC) should seek
safe shelter immediately!

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 13S and 16.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
